CIB Egypt, Palm Hills, Orascom Telecom: Egypt Equity Preview

-- B y   A h m e d   A   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-05-30T08:01:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-30/cib-egypt-palm-hills-orascom-telecom-egypt-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be active
in  Egypt ’s stock market. Symbols are in parentheses and prices
are from the last close.  The benchmark EGX 30 Index rose 2.5 percent to 5,548.06 in
Cairo.  Commercial International Bank Egypt SAE (COMI)  : The
central bank plans to submit amendments to the banking law that
would tighten corporate governance requirements for lenders to
the ruling military council within days,  Al Alam Al Youm 
newspaper reported, without saying where it got the information.
The new rules would ease restrictions on collecting non-
performing loans and require banks to disclose the 20 highest-
paid employees. The shares increased 1.8 percent to 31.83
Egyptian pounds.  Palm Hills Developments SAE (PHDC)  : The Cairo-based
real-estate developer was cut to “sell” from “neutral” at
EFG-Hermes Holding SAE because of legal disputes on land
purchases and concern over meeting delivery targets. The stock’s
fair value was set at 2.1 pounds. The shares gained 7.4 percent
to 2.33 pounds.  Orascom Telecom Holding SAE (ORTE)  : The valuation of the
Algerian unit of North Africa’s biggest mobile-network operator
is almost complete,  Algeria ’s Prime Minister Ahmed Ouyahia said
yesterday. The Algerian government plans to buy the unit, known
as Djezzy, he said. The shares advanced 0.9 percent to 4.37
pounds.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  